comments: I took Brenda\'s Medical Dosing/Calculations course. She is a no-nonsense down-to-business instructor, and I like that. She grades homework and tests right away, and is more than willing to help when you have questions. I wish more instructors were like her. Be sure to take advantage of the tutoring hours before class too, as this helps for exams.

comments: Brenda is great. She is approachable and makes you feel like you can be a nurse and will help you get there. I love my new role!

comments: She was the director of my nursing program and is likely the reason I felt so comfortable. I could approach her with pretty much any issue and she would advocate for you. I\'m gonna miss the program but I graduated and ready to start my nursing career!

comments: Brenda was awesome! All the material is made up by the State so can\'t really blame her for the tests or anything. She tries to make it as fun as possible. You HAVE to show up for class and do fairly well on chapter tests. But again these are the states standards for Nursing Assistants not hers. She was awesome though.

tag_professor: Respected (3)  Caring (2)  Gives good feedback (2)  LOTS OF HOMEWORK (1)
comments: I took the Nursing Assistant course with Brenda, and really enjoyed it. She was knowledgeable, and had a lot of experience in the field and teaching. She made it a fun, fairly easy class while stressing the importance of attendance and the seriousness of learning.
